      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: move theme script from <head> to <body> to prevent SSR hydration mismatch",
        "body": "TanStack Start manages `<head>` during SSR via `HeadContent`. Having an inline `<script>` tag as a sibling of `HeadContent` causes the SSR output to diverge from the client render, producing a hydration mismatch:\n```\n<head>\n  <HeadContent>\n+   <script suppressHydrationWarning={true}>\n-   {\"\\n\"}\n```\n\nFix: place the theme script as the first child of `<body>` instead of inside `<head>`. Inline scripts in `<body>` execute synchronously before the rest of the DOM is processed, so theme flash prevention (FOUC) is preserved.\n\nAlso adds `AGENTS.md` with project stack, commands, conventions, and the script-in-body rule for future AI agents working on this codebase.",
